title: Laboratory Low Voltage Supply
items.abstract: <jats:p>Nowadays there is little need to argue the case for providing a low voltage system in science laboratories â€” for physics at least. However, there is still much argument about the relative merits of different low voltage systems and it is difficult to choose between them. This article attempts to clarify the problem in three ways: first, it outlines the main features which are desirable in any low voltage system, then it attempts a comparison of some commonly used low voltage systems with respect to these and certain other important criteria, and finally it describes a new unit which seems close to providing a solution to the problem.</jats:p>
